  "prompt": "What are examples of socio-economic issues?",
  "response": "Socio-economic issues are problems that arise as a result of the interplay between social and economic factors. Some examples include:\n\n1. Poverty: Lack of access to basic resources, including food, shelter, and healthcare, can lead to malnutrition, homelessness, and disease.\n\n2. Income inequality: The unequal distribution of income and opportunity can lead to social and economic instability.\n\n3. Unemployment: High levels of unemployment can lead to poverty, social unrest, and crime.\n\n4. Discrimination: Discrimination based on race, gender, or other factors can limit opportunities and access to resources, leading to poverty and social exclusion.\n\n5. Education: Inadequate access to education can limit opportunities for social and economic advancement.\n\n6. Healthcare: Lack of access to affordable healthcare can lead to poor health outcomes and reduced productivity.\n\n7. Housing: Inadequate or unaffordable housing can lead to homelessness and poor health outcomes.\n\n8. Crime: High levels of crime can limit economic growth and social stability.\n\n9. Environmental degradation: Pollution and other forms of environmental degradation can lead to poor health outcomes and reduced economic opportunities.\n\n10. Political instability: Political instability can lead to economic uncertainty and reduced investment, limiting opportunities for growth and development.",
